  "body": "Thanks to @nicksavers for finding this!\r\n\r\nIn the `cmd/pics/state.go`, the visualisation of the block witness: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/blob/6e880cc945452c93001cf359380da3b85ef96669/cmd/pics/state.go#L596\r\n\r\nDisplays the values (in the leaves) that correspond to the state AFTER the block execution, and not BEFORE. This is most probably due to the fact that the `quadTrie` produced here:\r\nhttps://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/blob/6e880cc945452c93001cf359380da3b85ef96669/cmd/pics/state.go#L544\r\n\r\nstill shares the leaves with the state trie that gets modified.\r\nFix should be quite easy - make function `HexToQuad` in `trie/visual.go` create copies of the leaves.\r\n\r\nIn order to re-run the pictures, these commands are required:\r\n````\r\nmake pics\r\n./build/bin/pics -pic initialState1\r\n````\r\nyou would need graphviz installed for this to work. Pictures should appear in the current directory.",
